'''''Another Language''''' is the third [[studio album]] by American [[post-rock]] band [[This Will Destroy You]]. It was released on September 12, 2014, by [[Suicide Squeeze Records]]. ''Another Language'' was preceded by the digital release of two singles, "Dustism" and "Invitation".

== Background and production ==
According to a press release published by Suicide Squeeze Records, the album was recorded after a "prolonged vacuous dark period that threatened to break both the band and the members themselves".<ref>{{cite web|title=This Will Destroy You Details New Album, Shares "Dustism"|url=http://suicidesqueezerecords.tumblr.com/post/89673470146/this-will-destroy-you-details-new-album-shares|website=[[Tumblr]]|publisher=[[Suicide Squeeze Records]]|accessdate=August 18, 2014|date=June 23, 2014}}</ref> In February 2013, one of the band's guitarists, Jeremy Galindo, said that the band had started writing the next studio album.<ref>{{cite web|last1=P|first1=Gilbert|title=Interview: Jeremy Galindo, This Will Destroy You|url=http://echoesanddust.com/2013/02/interview-jeremy-galindo-this-will-destroy-you/|website=Echoesanddust.com|accessdate=August 18, 2014|date=February 2013}}</ref> Nine months later, the band said they were halfway done with the recording process.<ref name=nbhap>{{cite web|last1=Helbig|first1=Robert|title=Interview: This Will Destroy You <U+2013> The new album is halfway there|url=http://nbhap.com/music/interviews/this-will-destroy-you/|website=[[Nothing But Hope And Passion]]|accessdate=August 18, 2014|date=November 25, 2013}}</ref> In February 2014, the band's bassist
Donovan Jones reported that they were still working on the album.<ref>{{cite web|title=Interview: Donovan of This Will Destroy You|url=http://coreymcd22.wordpress.com/2014/02/21/interview-donovan-of-this-will-destroy-you/|website=Coreymcd22.wordpress.com|publisher=[[Wordpress]]|accessdate=August 18, 2014|date=February 21, 2014}}</ref>

== Composition ==
According to the band, ''Another Language'''s sound is "more upbeat and rhythmic" than their previous work.<ref name=nbhap/> They also described the sound of the album with the genre "doomgaze", a [[portmanteau]] of the words [[doom metal]] and [[shoegaze]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Yung|first1=Phillip|title=Take a peak into This Will Destroy You's upcoming album 'Another Language'|url=http://www.earmilk.com/2014/08/13/take-a-peak-into-this-will-destroy-yous-upcoming-album-another-language/|website=Earmilk.com|accessdate=August 18, 2014|date=August 13, 2014}}</ref>

== Release and promotion ==
The release and album artwork of the album were announced on June 23, 2014, with the release of the first single, "Dustism".<ref name=stereogum>{{cite web|last1=Bowe|first1=Miles|title=This Will Destroy You <U+2013> <U+201C>Dustism<U+201D> (Stereogum Premiere)|url=http://www.stereogum.com/1688222/this-will-destroy-you-dustism-stereogum-premiere/mp3s/|website=[[Stereogum]]|accessdate=August 18, 2014|date=June 23, 2014}}</ref> The album's second single, "Invitation", was released on August 11.<ref>{{cite web|title=Listen to a Song from This Will Destroy You's (Obviously) Epic New Album|url=http://noisey.vice.com/blog/this-will-destroy-you-invitation-song-premiere|website=Noisey|publisher=[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]|accessdate=August 18, 2014|date=August 11, 2014}}</ref> ''Another Language'' was made available for streaming through [[Pitchfork Media]] on September 8. A video to accompany the album was directed by Sean Miller and Christopher Royal King.<ref>{{cite web|title=Our new album Another Language is...|url=https://www.facebook.com/thiswilldestroyyou/posts/731899570198331|website=[[This Will Destroy You]]|publisher=[[Facebook]]|accessdate=September 8, 2014|date=September 8, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=This Will Destroy You: Another Language|url=http://pitchfork.com/advance/530-another-language/|website=[[Pitchfork Media]]|accessdate=September 8, 2014|date=September 8, 2014}}</ref>

Prior to the album release, This Will Destroy You announced a worldwide concert and festival tour, with support from Future Death and Silent Land Time Machine in North America, and Thought Forms and [[Lymbyc Systym]] in Europe.<ref name=stereogum/><ref>{{cite web|title=THIS WILL DESTROY YOU European tour 2014|url=http://www.littlebig-agency.net/blog/this-will-destroy-you-announces-european-tour/|website=LittleBig Agency|accessdate=September 8, 2014|date=May 29, 2014}}</ref>

